---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base>
  <!-- ============ Hero ============ -->
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">
        <span class="chip">New</span>
        <span>Tiptap-powered editor — now in beta</span>
      </div>
      <h1>A calm place for the work in <em>your head</em>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Notable is a notes app built for writing, not arranging. A rich editor that gets out of the
        way, fast search across everything you've ever written, and quiet sync between your devices.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="#cta" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Start writing — it's free</a>
        <a href="#editor" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">See the editor</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-foot">
        <span class="dot"></span>
        No credit card · Your data, your export, anytime
      </div>

      <!-- Hero preview -->
      <div class="preview-wrap">
        <div class="preview">
          <div class="preview-top">
            <span class="preview-dot r"></span>
            <span class="preview-dot y"></span>
            <span class="preview-dot g"></span>
            <span class="preview-title">notable.app — Q3 roadmap — first draft</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mini-app">
            <aside class="mini-side">
              <div class="group">
                <div class="label">Library</div>
                <div class="mini-row active"><span class="swatch"></span> All notes <span class="count">128</span></div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch"></span> Starred <span class="count">12</span></div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch"></span> Recent</div>
              </div>
              <div class="group">
                <div class="label">Tags</div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch blue"></span> Work <span class="count">34</span></div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch green"></span> Personal <span class="count">21</span></div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch pink"></span> Ideas <span class="count">17</span></div>
                <div class="mini-row"><span class="swatch violet"></span> Reading <span class="count">9</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <section class="mini-list">
              <div class="mini-card active">
                <div class="ttl">Q3 roadmap — first draft</div>
                <div class="snip">
                  Three pillars for the quarter: reliability, onboarding velocity, and the new
                  collaboration surface…
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mini-card">
                <div class="ttl">Notes from coffee with Maya</div>
                <div class="snip">
                  She's leaving the platform team in June to start something in the dev-tools space…
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mini-card">
                <div class="ttl">Books to read this summer</div>
                <div class="snip">
                  A Pattern Language · Christopher Alexander. The Beginning of Infinity · David
                  Deutsch…
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mini-card">
                <div class="ttl">Idea: weekly digest of small wins</div>
                <div class="snip">
                  What if the team had a Friday ritual where each person shares one small thing that
                  worked…
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
            <article class="mini-editor">
              <h2>Q3 product roadmap — first draft</h2>
              <div class="meta">
                <span>May 22 · 10:42</span>
                <span class="pill-tag">Work</span>
                <span class="pill-tag">Planning</span>
              </div>
              <p>
                This is a working draft. The goal is to land on three pillars by end of week so each
                owning team has time to write their own one-pager.
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li><strong>Reliability.</strong> Cut p99 latency on the read path by 30%.</li>
                <li><strong>Onboarding velocity.</strong> Reach the "first useful moment" inside ten minutes.</li>
                <li><strong>Collaboration surface.</strong> Ship the shared-cursor MVP behind a flag by August.</li>
              </ol>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ============ Built in the open ============ -->
  <section class="proof">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="proof-label">Built in the open · v0.1 beta</div>
      <p class="open-note">
        Notable is brand new. There are no testimonials yet, no celebrity users, no "trusted by
        Fortune 500" badge. There is one person making it, a public changelog, and a promise to
        email you back.
        <br />
        <a href="#" class="open-link">Read the changelog →</a>
        <span class="open-sep">·</span>
        <a href="#" class="open-link">Follow the build</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Features ============ -->
  <section id="features">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Why Notable</div>
        <h2>The tools you need, none of the friction.</h2>
        <p>
          Most notes apps are content management systems in a trench coat. Notable is just a great
          place to write — fast, organized, and quietly synced.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="features">
        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 19l7-7 3 3-7 7-3-3z"></path>
              <path d="M18 13l-1.5-7.5L2 2l3.5 14.5L13 18l5-5z"></path>
              <path d="M2 2l7.586 7.586"></path>
              <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="2"></circle>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>An editor that disappears</h3>
          <p>
            Headings, lists, checklists, code, tables, math. All the structure you want — and not a
            single floating toolbar in your peripheral vision.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"></circle>
              <line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"></line>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Search that actually finds it</h3>
          <p>
            Full-text and fuzzy search across every note you've ever written. Typos forgiven. Tag
            filters, date filters, and instant results.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"></polyline>
              <polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"></polyline>
              <path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0114.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0020.49 15"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Sync without the spinner</h3>
          <p>
            Edit on your laptop, finish on your phone. Notable saves as you type and reconciles
            silently — no merge dialogs, no waiting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M20.59 13.41l-7.17 7.17a2 2 0 01-2.83 0L2 12V2h10l8.59 8.59a2 2 0 010 2.82z"></path>
              <line x1="7" y1="7" x2="7.01" y2="7"></line>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Tags, not folders</h3>
          <p>
            Notes resist hierarchy. Tag them with as many ideas as fit, filter on intersections, and
            stop pretending your thoughts are tidy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"></rect>
              <path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0110 0v4"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Your data, your keys</h3>
          <p>
            Notes are yours. Export to Markdown or JSON whenever. Self-host on your own server in an
            afternoon, or let us host it for you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <div class="feature-icon">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"></polyline>
              <polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Built for keyboards</h3>
          <p>
            Every action has a shortcut. Slash-commands for blocks, <kbd>⌘K</kbd> for jump-to-note,
            fold sections, drag without lifting your hands.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Editor showcase ============ -->
  <section id="editor" style="background: var(--bg-2);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split">
        <div class="split-copy">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">The editor</div>
          <h3>Words first. Everything else, when you ask.</h3>
          <p>
            Notable's editor is built on Tiptap — the same engine that powers Linear, GitLab, and a
            dozen tools you already use. Headings, lists, blockquotes, code blocks, tables, task
            lists, embeds. They're all there. None of them are in your way.
          </p>
          <div class="bullets">
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Slash commands.</strong>
                <span>Type <code>/</code> anywhere to insert a heading, list, code block, callout, or table — no menus.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Markdown in, beautiful out.</strong>
                <span>Type <code>##</code> and it becomes a heading. Type <code>- [ ]</code> and you get a checkbox. Muscle memory preserved.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Code that looks like code.</strong>
                <span>Syntax highlighting for 100+ languages, with a copy button you'll actually find.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="split-visual">
          <div class="visual-toolbar">
            <div class="tb-btn">H1</div>
            <div class="tb-btn on">B</div>
            <div class="tb-btn italic">I</div>
            <div class="tb-divider"></div>
            <div class="tb-btn">≡</div>
            <div class="tb-btn">⁝</div>
            <div class="tb-divider"></div>
            <div class="tb-btn">"</div>
            <div class="tb-btn">{ }</div>
          </div>
          <div class="visual-body">
            <h4>Open questions</h4>
            <p>
              A roadmap is not a list of features. It's a story about what the team is going to
              learn this quarter — and what we're willing to be wrong about.
            </p>
            <div class="task done">
              <span class="box">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Confirm reliability owner with the platform team</span>
            </div>
            <div class="task done">
              <span class="box">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span>Get latency baseline numbers from analytics</span>
            </div>
            <div class="task">
              <span class="box"></span>
              <span>Decide whether onboarding includes the template gallery</span>
            </div>
            <div class="task">
              <span class="box"></span>
              <span>Identify three design partners for collab preview</span>
            </div>
            <blockquote>"Specificity is the soul of narrative." — John Hodgman</blockquote>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Search showcase ============ -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split reverse">
        <div class="split-copy">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Search</div>
          <h3>Find that thing you wrote, six months ago, at 2am.</h3>
          <p>
            Postgres-backed full-text search with ranked results, typo tolerance, and tag filters.
            You can stop archiving things in case you "need them later." Just write. We'll find it
            again.
          </p>
          <div class="bullets">
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Instant.</strong>
                <span>Results in under 50ms across thousands of notes. Search-as-you-type, no enter key required.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Forgiving.</strong>
                <span>Misspelled it the first time too? Trigram matching finds the note anyway.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bullet">
              <span class="check">
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <div>
                <strong>Scoped.</strong>
                <span>Filter by tag, by date, by starred. Combine them. Save the query as a smart view.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="split-visual search-visual">
          <div class="search-bar">
            <svg
              width="16"
              height="16"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              style="color: var(--text-faint)"
            >
              <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"></circle>
              <line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"></line>
            </svg>
            <input value="latency baseline" readonly />
            <kbd>⌘ K</kbd>
          </div>
          <div class="search-results">
            <div class="sr-item hi">
              <div class="sr-ttl">Q3 product roadmap — first draft</div>
              <div class="sr-snip">
                …get <mark>latency baseline</mark> numbers from analytics. Reliability is non-negotiable…
              </div>
              <div class="sr-meta">Work · Planning · today</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sr-item">
              <div class="sr-ttl">Migration runbook — staging</div>
              <div class="sr-snip">
                …run the schema diff against the read replica first to confirm <mark>latency</mark> shape…
              </div>
              <div class="sr-meta">Work · May 12</div>
            </div>
            <div class="sr-item">
              <div class="sr-ttl">Notes from coffee with Maya</div>
              <div class="sr-snip">
                …the offline-first sync work we did had unusual <mark>baseline</mark> characteristics…
              </div>
              <div class="sr-meta">Personal · Yesterday</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Quote ============ -->
  <section class="quote-section" style="background: var(--bg-2);">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="big-quote">
        "I stopped opening five different apps to think. I just open Notable. That's the whole
        review."
      </p>
      <div class="quote-attr">— a writer who asked us not to publish their name</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Pricing ============ -->
  <section id="pricing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Pricing</div>
        <h2>Honest, small numbers.</h2>
        <p>
          Free for personal use, forever. Pay only if you need more devices, more storage, or to
          share with a team.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing">
        <div class="price-card">
          <div class="price-name">Free</div>
          <div class="price-tag">$0 <span class="per">/ forever</span></div>
          <div class="price-desc">Everything you need to think in writing.</div>
          <ul class="price-list">
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Up to 500 notes</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Two devices, synced</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Full editor, tags, search</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Export to Markdown & JSON</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#cta" class="btn btn-outline">Start free</a>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card feat">
          <div class="price-name">Personal</div>
          <div class="price-tag">$5 <span class="per">/ month</span></div>
          <div class="price-desc">For people who actually keep their notes.</div>
          <ul class="price-list">
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Unlimited notes</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Unlimited devices</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Attachments up to 100MB</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Daily encrypted backups</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Version history (90 days)</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#cta" class="btn btn-primary">Start 14-day trial</a>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card">
          <div class="price-name">Team</div>
          <div class="price-tag">$9 <span class="per">/ person / month</span></div>
          <div class="price-desc">Write together, without the meetings.</div>
          <ul class="price-list">
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Everything in Personal</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Shared collections</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Co-editing & comments</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> SSO (SAML / Google)</li>
            <li><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Admin controls & audit log</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#cta" class="btn btn-outline">Talk to us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
  <section id="faq" style="background: var(--bg-2);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Questions</div>
        <h2>Reasonable things to ask.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq">
        <details open>
          <summary>Can I self-host Notable?</summary>
          <p>
            Yes. Notable's server is a single Docker Compose file — Postgres, a Node API, and Caddy
            for TLS. Pull the image, set three environment variables, point a domain at it.
            Personal-use license is free; commercial self-hosting is included with the Team plan.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What happens to my data if I leave?</summary>
          <p>
            One click exports every note as Markdown, with all attachments, in a single zip. There's
            also a JSON export that preserves the full Tiptap document structure, if you want to
            migrate it somewhere structured. Your data is never held hostage.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Does Notable work offline?</summary>
          <p>
            Reading and editing existing notes works offline — the app keeps a local copy in your
            browser. Sync resumes silently when you're back online. Full offline-first sync with
            conflict resolution is coming in Notable 2.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How is search so fast?</summary>
          <p>
            Postgres full-text search with a GIN-indexed <code>tsvector</code> column, plus a
            <code>pg_trgm</code> index for typo tolerance. We're not running an external search
            service — it's just Postgres doing what Postgres does well. Most queries return in under
            20ms even with tens of thousands of notes.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Is it really free, forever?</summary>
          <p>
            The free plan stays free. We make money on Personal and Team plans for people who want
            more storage, more devices, or shared workspaces. We will not run ads, sell data, or
            invent a paywall around features you already use.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ Final CTA ============ -->
  <section id="cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-banner">
        <h2>Stop arranging. Start writing.</h2>
        <p>It takes thirty seconds. It might take a habit.</p>
        <div class="hero-ctas" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
          <a href="/app/login" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Create your account</a>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Read the docs →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
